      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;div&gt;You got it about right bro.  The thought way as well, but the way the penalty goes is this:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Ex: Mantle of Pure Spirit gives 30% healing up to level 67, and -10% each level above.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;You take your 30% healing bonus (because in essence this is 100% bonus).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;10% of 30 = 3%. &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;This is the only part I'm not 100% sure about.  If the -10% each level is -3% for level 68, another -3% for 69, and -3% for 70%.  This would be -9%, which would still give you a 21% Healing Benefit, which is still &amp;gt; Ground Healers Stone (20%).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I believe the penalty scales tho so here's what it would really be I believe:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;10% of 30 = 3%        so any level 68 spell would get 27% Healing Increase.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;10% of 27 = 2.7%     so any level 69 spell would get 24.3% Healing Increase&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;10% of 24.3 = 2.4%  so any level 70 spell would get 21.9/22.0% Healing Increase&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;As you can see, either way the Mantle &amp;gt; Aug so that should show ya the game is acting correctly when it always lights up your mantle over your aug.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;It is easy to prove which method to determine the penalty is correct.... check spell haste focii.  Spell Haste works 100% every time, so depending on how much you save off your spells will determine.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Warrdance on &lt;span class="date_text"&gt;03-06-2006&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="time_text"&gt;11:20 AM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
