      <title>Re: Maybe a player or developer type can answer</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=11048#M11048</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Something else to consider:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;clerics get four instant healing spells at the upper levels:  Pious Remedy at 66th, Pious Light at 68th, and Ancient: Hallowed Light and Desperate Renewal at level 70.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;DesRen is not a very good heal spell and therefore very few clerics actually use it, so you can pretty much take it out of the equation when trying to figure out what the best healing bonus focus effect is for you.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ancient: hallowed light is only available to those who are Anguish and/or Demi-Plane flagged (RSS king and queen can drop the ancient runes but they are VERY rare).  And if you have those flags then you are most likely in a guild that has done or can do the various Qvic, and Txevu mobs in order to get the drops to get the Drakkmor's Vambraces of the Divine with the Discordant Healing focus (45% healing bonus to 68), or the last blood augment for DoN cultural armor that gets you a 50% healing bonus to level 70.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;My point is, unless you have and active use Ancient: hallowed light or Desperate renewal a healing bonus focus effect to level 67 should be sufficient, you would only lose 10% of the bonus to Pious Light.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
